items.title: Dodgers clinch postseason, end losing streak
items.summary: Clayton Kershaw stopped the nonsense Tuesday night, pitching and batting and even running the Dodgers into the postseason. A 5-3 win over the Giants at AT&T Park clinched an October berth for the Dodgers, ended a historic 11-game losing streak and cut the magic number for a fifth consecutive division title to eight.

items.title: Dipoto checks out Ohtani on Japan scouting trip
items.summary: Every move by Japanese two-way star Shohei Ohtani figures to be monitored closely by Major League scouts and executives in the coming months. The Mariners, apparently, intend to be one of the interested parties, as general manager Jerry Dipoto was in Tokyo to watch Ohtani pitch on Tuesday morning.
